Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1/2} into 2 cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve the @yellow pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Using your hands, break up the @pork sausage meat{225%g} into bite-sized chunks, about 2cm.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large, wide bottomed #saucepan{} over medium high heat. Cook the sausage chunks until browned on all sides, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn frequently. Add the sweet potato and pepper, stir to combine. Sprinkle on the @paprika{1/2%tsp} and the @dried oregano{1/2%tsp} and stir through. Stir in the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1/2}. 

Add the @chicken stock powder{1/2%stock cube} and the @water{200%ml}. Bring the mixture to the boil. Stir to dissolve the stock powder then lower the heat to medium. Pop a #lid{} on and cook until the sweet potato is tender and the sausage is cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausage is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Slice the @ciabatta{1} in half (as if you are making a sandwich) and place on a lined #baking tray{}. In a #small bowl{}, mix the @garlic{1%clove} with the @oil{} and season with @pepper{}. Spoon the oil over the ciabatta, then sprinkle the cheese on top. Ten mins before the ragu is ready, bake the garlic bread on the top shelf of your oven until the cheese is golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Five minutes before everything is ready, heat a #frying pan{} over medium heat and add the @unsalted butter{30%g}. Allow it to melt then add the @mangetout{150%g}. Toss to coat in the butter and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{} and cover the pan with a lid or #foil{}. Steam until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When the ragu is ready, taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it is necessary. Share between your bowls. Serve the mangetout on top. Cut the cheesy garlic bread into wedges and dive in!

> Remember, sharing, is caring. Enjoy!